---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import NewsletterSignup from '../../components/NewsletterSignup.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="The Drive Home Playbook"
  description="A free 12-page guide. The exact words to say in the first 90 seconds after a game, by sport and by age."
>
  <section class="border-b border-ink bg-ink text-paper">
    <div class="container-px py-20 grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-10 items-end">
      <div class="md:col-span-7">
        <p class="font-display italic text-trophy mb-3" style="font-weight: 500;">Free · 12 pages · PDF</p>
        <h1 class="font-display text-paper text-[2.5rem] md:text-[4.5rem] leading-[1.0]" style="font-weight: 500;">
          The Drive Home <em class="text-rust">Playbook</em>.
        </h1>
        <p class="font-display text-paper-warm text-xl md:text-2xl mt-8 max-w-xl leading-snug">
          The first 90 seconds after a youth game decide what the next week feels like in your house. This guide tells you exactly what to say, by sport and by age.
        </p>
        <p class="font-display italic text-paper-warm mt-6 text-base" style="font-weight: 500;">
          Drop your email below. We'll send you the PDF and add you to the weekly note. Easy unsubscribe.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-5">
        <NewsletterSignup
          variant="card"
          headline="Send me the playbook"
          blurb="One subscribe, two things in your inbox: the playbook now, and one short read a week from the editorial desk."
          buttonLabel="Send the playbook"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-b border-bone">
    <div class="container-px py-16 grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-10">
      <div class="md:col-span-4">
        <p class="font-display italic text-rust" style="font-weight: 500;">What's inside</p>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-8 article-body">
        <p>The 90-second rule. Why the window is so short and what's actually happening in your kid's head while it's open.</p>
        <p>Eight scripted opening lines, by sport. Baseball. Softball. Soccer. Basketball. Football. Hockey. Lacrosse. Volleyball. Each one tested by parent-coaches in our network.</p>
        <p>Bonus: scripts for theater, choir, and dance, because the same rule fits the concert hall.</p>
        <p>Three things never to say in the car after a game.</p>
        <p>A printable pocket card you can keep in the glove box.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-b border-bone">
    <div class="container-px py-16 grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-10">
      <div class="md:col-span-4">
        <p class="font-display italic text-rust" style="font-weight: 500;">Why we made it</p>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-8 article-body">
        <p>We watched two kids grow up moving through eight sports, two theater programs, and one orchestra. The same pattern showed up everywhere. Most parents handle the game well. Most parents handle the drive home badly.</p>
        <p>The fix is small. The first 90 seconds. A different sentence. A different tone. We wrote it down.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <NewsletterSignup
    headline="Send the playbook"
    blurb="One short note a week, plus the playbook in your inbox right now."
    buttonLabel="Subscribe"
  />
</BaseLayout>
